<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
<tr>
	<td width="1%">&nbsp;</td>
	<td width="98%">
  
		<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
		<tr>
		    <td valign="top">
		     <p><font face="Verdana" size="3"><b>Article Title:</b>&nbsp;</font>
		     <font face="Verdana" size="2">Quick infobits from Brad</font><br>
		     <a href = "../Subscribe.asp?DID=107157" ><font face="Verdana" size="2">[Subscribe to this document]</font></a></p>
			 </td>
		</tr>
		
		<tr><td>&nbsp;</tr><tr>
		
		    <td valign="top"><div style= "padding:4;float: right"> <script language=JavaScript src=http://www.obsidian-tech.com/absolutebm/abmx.aspx?z=26></script></div><p><font face="Verdana" size="2">
		    <Blockquote>
 BTW all. I just wanted to note here my feelings on the people from verant that reply in this and other boards (Brad, Gordon, etc.). They are PR (Public Relations) for Verant. All big companies have them, all politicians have them. They have a second name, It's Spin Doctor. They take the facts and "spin" them into something to feed to the public that isn't as damaging as the real facts. They lie with every breath they take. Trust what you know about a given event etc. Not what someone else explains it to be (IE. There is no zone bug between QH/WK) =)<P>

 PL<P>
 
<B>but there IS a zone bug between QH and WK.<P>
 
ack! there goes your theory, sorry :)<P>
 
-Brad</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><I>**Some mobs DO have missile weapons. Are you suggesting that more should, and that we should increase the damage they can do with ranged weapons? " --Aradune</B></I><P>

Brad,<P>

To answer your question: Yes.<P>

In spite of the numerous attempts to prevent "safe killing", kiting has simply taken a new turn. Now it's "Snare-kiting" or "reverse kiting". Granted, you will never be able to handle EVERY situation, but certainly some monsters would benefit greatly by the addition of missiles. Giants should throw huge boulders, humanoid-types should have a chance of using normal missile weapons, perhaps even a few special non-magical unique attacks (a manticore with tail-bolts, or something with longer "reach")<P>

Again, it would not solve every problem, and would not be a final answer - but it would create variety, and force people to rethink "snare-kiting" those hill giants (I watched a Druid solo from 40th to 49th that way). If the solution to stopping a creature from using it's "devastating missile attack" is to engage it in melee, I think people would be more inclined to melee - wouldn't you?<P>

<B>What does everyone else think of this?<P>

-Brad</B><P>

<a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/029952.html">Link to thread</a>
</blockquote>
		    </font></p>
			 </td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
