			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				There are plenty of arguments for and against kiting. It doesn't take long in SK to observe PCs getting discouraged with all the druids plucking Avocets out of the tree and kiting them away. But I think kiting is still a good part of the game. Grouping/community aside, the more variety there is, the better the game can be. Heck, I even spend up to 15 minutes on a single kill kiting it with a Darkwood bow (I'm a ranger). Though it takes a long time, there's some satisfaction in soloing an NPC that cons red =).<BR>
<BR>
For many classes, limiting or eliminating kiting would be beneficial, but why are we asking Verant to nerf something? Hehe, I thought that was one of our greatest fears...
				</font>
