	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I think missile weapons are long overdue, though I can only imagine how difficult it would be to code for a new form of warfare.<BR>
Historically, specifically medievally, there were entire tribes and peoples who relied largely on the ranged attack in warfare. English longbowmen come immediately to mind: the range of the huge yew bows gave English troops a first strike capability nearly as critical in the 1200s as nuclear first strike would be seven hundred years later. In game, a group of mobs with long-range projectile arms would significantly alter the tactics of many an adventurer, especially if that long, complicated DoT were interrupted by a nice arrow through the skull.<BR>
Variations on heavy-damage ranged weapons have been extant for millenia. Whereas hill giants could rely upon brute strength to loft boulders toward foes and innocent bystanders alike, man has had to fashion works - ballistae, catapaults, siege engines. Which brings to mind some great events...like Fippy Darkpaw leading a train of towers hurling Greek fire and flaming stones upon the good city of Qeynos...<BR>
nah...it'd never happen. ::grin::
				</font>
			</td>

